list.item:
Drug interactions — The concomitant use of metformin hydrochloride extended-release tablets with specific drugs may increase the risk of metformin-associated lactic acidosis: those that impair renal function, result in significant hemodynamic change, interfere with acid-base balance, or increase metformin accumulation [see 

   Drug Interactions (7)
]. Consider more frequent monitoring of patients.

text.paragraph:
Metformin hydrochloride extended-release tablets are not recommended in patients with hepatic impairment [

                              see Warnings and Precautions (5.1)
                            ].
